Add a Mojo JSON round-trip check to CI using the shared round-trip fixture, run with ``mojo run``.  Because Mojo ships no standard JSON encoder, the helper hand-rolls one: the shared input's mixed-type top-level object is literalized with the ``VARIANT`` heterogeneous strategy and re-emitted by a shape-driven walk that reads each value from the ``Variant`` slot matching its original JSON type.  The wide ``biginteger`` field (which overflows Mojo's 64-bit ``Int``) and the array/object fields (which the ``VARIANT`` strategy cannot place alongside scalars in one dict) are excluded.
